-- Oil Companies Want to Sell $90 Billion of Assets, FT Reports
-- B y   A l a n   P u r k i s s
-- 2010-12-28T06:36:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-28/oil-companies-want-to-sell-90-billion-of-assets-ft-reports.html
Oil and gas assets worth more than
$90 billion globally are on the market as companies such as  BP
Plc , Royal Dutch Shell Plc,  ExxonMobil Corp . and ConocoPhillips
have put sizable portfolios of assets up for sale, the Financial
Times reported, citing figures from Derrick Petroleum Services,
a consulting firm.  In mid-2009 the figure was $20 billion and a year ago it
was $46 billion, the newspaper said.  Most of the assets are being disposed of to pay for
exploration and production programs, the FT said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alan Purkiss  in London on   apurkiss@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge in London at   ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 